track.name: Don't Leave Home
comments: Jesus. I never realized it was about a drug. Now this song took a really dark turn. Can't stop thinking about that now when I listen to it. I still love the song though.
this is definitely a "song about drug addiction told from the drug's point of view".
The best part is how deceptively sweet and friendly the song sounds on top of that. [2]
A song about drug addiction told from the drug's point of view? this is such an awesome idea. [4]
Definitely my favourite off the album.
Starker Titel, starkes Mädel, die muss man lieben!
Her voice is one of the most beautiful sounds out there.
"Don't Leave Home" and "White Flag" are my Dido's favorite singles
